What is String?
String is not a keyword in java. String final class in java. lang package. 

 final is keyword in java 
final with variable -  cant not change variable value. 
final with class name-  cant inherit that that. 
 final with methods.. -- cannot override that method. 

 final int a=10;
int a=50;

How many ways to create string objects in java?
there two ways:- 
1. using new operator.
2. using string literals.

String s= new String("welcome");// using will create new string object 
String s1= "welcome" // using this it will search in memory is there any object "welcome" is present or not ? . if it is present this will point out that value. but if no then create new object. 

 String is immutable ---> cannot modify, cannot change . for security we can store sensitive data.
here paste code----------

 
Java STRING COMPARISON 
by equals --compare content 
by ==operator -- compare reference 
 STRING BUFFER AND STRING BUILDER ( most important )
 CLASS --- BOTH ARE MUTABLE 
 string BUFFER - SYNCHRONIZED , SLOW
 string BUILDER - NON SYNCHRONIZE, FASTER THAN BUFFER
 difference between string and string buffer?
 string is immutable and string buffer is. mutable. 




